obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (46931)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Interpretation clause.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46931&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `The following words and expressions in this Act shall have the`
  line `meaning assigned to them, unless there be something in the subject or context repugnant to such`
  line `construction, that is to say--`
  line
  line `the words "Magistrate of the district" shall mean the chief officer charged with the executive`
  line `administration of a district and exercising the powers of a Magistrate, by whatever designation the`
  line `chief officer charged with such executive administration is styled:`
  line
  line `the word " Magistrate" shall include all persons within the general police-district, exercising all or`
  line `any of the power of a Magistrate:`
  line
  line `the word "police" shall include all persons who shall be enrolled under this Act:`
  line
  line `the words "general police-district" shall embrace any^1`
  line `presidency, ^2`
  line `[State] or place, or any part of`
  line `any presidency, ^3`
  line `[State] or place, in which this Act shall be ordered to take effect:`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[the words "District Superintendent" and "District Superintendent of Police" shall include any`
  line `Assistant District Superintendent or other person appointed by general or special order of the ^5[State]`
  line `Government] to perform all or any of the duties of a District Superintendent of Police under this Act`
  line `in any district:]`
  line
  line `the word "property" shall include any moveable property money, or valuable security:`
  line
  line ^6
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `the word "person" shall include a company or corporation:`
  line
  line `the word "month" shall mean a calendar month:`
  line
  line ^7
  line `the word "cattle" shall, besides horned cattle, include elephants, camels, horses, asses, mules,`
  line `sheep, goats and swine.`
  line
  line ^8
  line `[References to the subordinate ranks of a police force shall be construed as references to members`
  line `of that force below the rank of Deputy Superintendent.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Short title given by the Indian Short Titles Act, 1897 (14 of 1897).`
  line
  line `This Act has been applied to`
  line
  line `the Sonthal Parganas by the Sonthal Parganas Settlement Regulation,1872 (3 of 1872), s. 3;`
  line
  line `the Town of Calcutta and its suburbs, with modifications by the Calcutta Police Act, 1898 (Ben.1 of 1898);`
  line
  line `the Khondmals District by the Khondmals Laws Regulation, 1936 (4 of 1936), s. 3 and Schedule;`
  line
  line `the Angul District by the Angul Laws Regulation, 1936 (5 of 1936), s. 3 and Schedule; and`
  line
  line `the areas transferred to Orissa from the Madras Presidency, by the Orissa Laws Regulation, 1936 (1 of 1936).`
  line
  line `It has been declared, by notification under section 3 (a) of the Scheduled Districts Act, 1874 (14 of 1874), to be in force`
  line `in the following Scheduled Districts, namely:`
  line
  line `The District of Hazaribagh, Lohardaga (now the Ranchi District, see Calcutta Gazette, 1899 Part I, p.44) and Manbhum`
  line `and Pargana Dhalbhum and the Kolhan in the District of Singhbhum, see Gazette of India, 1881, Part I p.504, and the`
  line `Porahat Estate in the Singhbhum District, see Gazette of India, 1897, Part I, p 1059.`
  line
  line `It has been extended, by notification under s. 5 of the same Act, to the Kumaon and Garhwal Districts, see Gazette of`
  line `India, 1891, Part I, p.185, and (with the exception of s. 5) to the Scheduled District of Coorg, see Gazette of India, 1914,`
  line `Part II, p. 2347. Ss. 15, 15A, 16, 30, 30A, 31 and 32 have been extended to the Scheduled Districts in Ganjam and`
  line `Vizagapatam, see Fort St. George Gazette, 1898, Part I, p.667, and Gazette of India, 1898, Part I, p. 873.The whole Act has`
  line `been extended to the Amindivi Islands attached to the South Kanara District; see Fort St. George Gazette, 1935, Part I, p.`
  line 1202.
  line
  line `It has been extended to the Merged States and the States of Bhopal, Bilaspur, Himachal Pradesh and Kutch by the`
  line `Merged States (Laws) Act, 1949 (59 of 1949), and to the States of Manipur, Tripura and Vindhya Pradesh by the Part C`
  line `States (Laws) Act, 1950 (30 of 1950).`
  line
  line `It has been extend to`
  line
  line `(1) and brought into force in Dadra and Nagar Haveli (w.e.f. 1-7-1965) by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(2) Laccadive Minicoy and Amindivi Islands (w.e.f. 1-10-1967): vide Reg. 8 of 1965, s. 3 and Schedule;`
  line
  line `(3) the whole of Madhya Pardesh by M.P. Act 23 of 1958 (when notified); and`
  line
  line `(4) Goa, Daman and Diu with modifications, by Reg. 12 of 1962, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `As to special enactments in force in Madras, Bombay and Lower Provinces of Bengal, and extensions of this Act under`
  line `the power conferred by section 46, see notes to that section.`
  line
  line `As to special enactments for Military, Frontier or Rural Police in force in certain parts of the States, see footnote to`
  line `section 8.`
  line
  line `As to the creation of special police-districts embracing parts of two or more Provinces and the extension to every part`
  line `thereof the powers and jurisdiction of members of a police force belonging to any part of the States, see the Police Act, 1888`
  line `(3 of 1888).`
  line
  line `The Act has been amended in its application to`
  line
  line `the C.P. and Berar by C.P. and Berar Act 3 of 1937; Madras by Madras Act 13 of 1948; the U.P. by U.P. Acts 2 of`
  line `1939, 2 of 1944 and 32 of 1952; Punjab by E.P. Act 30 of 1948; Pondicherry by Pondicherry Act 7 of 1968; West Bengal`
  line `by West Bengal Act 5 of 1973; Orissa by Orissa Acts 5 of 1976 and 34 of 1976 and Sikkim by Skkim Act 7 of 1980.`
  line
  line `Repealed in its application to Bellary District by Mysore Act 14 of 1955.`
  line
  line `2. Under s. 2 of Police Act, 1888 (3 of 1888), the Central Government may, notwithstanding this provision, create a special`
  line `police-district, consisting of parts of two or more States.`
  line
  line `As to Delhi State, see Gazette of India, 1912, Pt. I, p. 1105.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Province".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 1.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G."`
  line
  line `6. The definitions relating to "number" and "gender" rep. By Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `7. Cf. Definition of "cattle" in s. 3 of the Cattle-trespass Act, 1871 (1 of 1871).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (46932)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Constitution of the force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46932&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^22. Constitution of the forces.-- The entire police-establishment under a ^1[State Government] shall`
  line `for the purposes of this Act, be deemed to be one ^3police force, and shall be formally enrolled; and`
  line `shall consist of such number of officers and men, and shall be constituted in such manner, ^4*** as`
  line `shall from time to time be ordered by the ^1[State Government] ^5***.`
  line
  line `^6[Subject to the provisions of this Act the pay and all other conditions of service of members of`
  line `the subordinate ranks of any police force shall be such as may-be determined by the 2[State]`
  line Government.]
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G."`
  line `2. S. 2, so far as it is related to the provinces under the administration of the Lieutenant-Governor of Bengal, rep. by the`
  line `Bengal Police Act, 1869 (Ben. 7 of 1869).`
  line `3. See note to s. 8, infra, as to enrolment of the police force in certain places.`
  line `4. The words and the members of such force shall receive such pay omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line `5. Certain words omitted, ibid.`
  line `6. Ins. ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (46933)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Superintendence in the State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46933&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Superintendence in the ^1[State Government].--The superintendence of the police throughout`
  line `a general police-district shall vest in and ^2*** shall be exercised by the ^1[State Government] to which`
  line `such district is subordinate; and except as authorised under the provisions of this Act, no person,`
  line `officer, or Court shall be empowered by the ^1[State Government] to ^3*** supersede, or control any`
  line `police functionary.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G."`
  line `2. See note to s. 8, infra, as to enrolment of the police force in certain places.`
  line `3. The word "appoint" omitted, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (46934)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Inspector-General of Police, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46934&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1The administration of the police throughout the general`
  line `police district shall be vested in an officer to be styled the Inspector-General of Police, and in such Deputy Inspectors-General and Assistant Inspectors-General as to the ^2`
  line `[State Government] shall been`
  line `seem fit.`
  line
  line `The administration of the police throughout the local jurisdiction of the Magistrate of the district`
  line `shall, under the general control and direction of such Magistrate, be vested in a District Superintendent`
  line `and such Assistant District Superintendents as the ^2`
  line `[State Government] shall consider necessary.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. In the town and suburbs of Calcutta, the administration of the police vests in the "Commissioner of Police",`
  line
  line `See s. 3 of the Calcutta Police Act, 1866 (Ben. 4 of 1866).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  line
  line `3. Certain words omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (46983)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Powers of Inspector General Exercise of power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46983&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Inspector-General of Police shall`
  line `have the full powers of a Magistrate throughout the general police-district; but shall exercise those`
  line `powers subject to such limitation as may from time to time be imposed by the ^1`
  line `[State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (46936)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46936&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `[Magisterial powers of police officers.] Rep. by the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1882 (Act 10 of`
  line `1882), s. 2 and Schedule I (b).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (46937)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Appointment, dismissal, etc., of inferior officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46937&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^2[^3[Subject to the provisions of Article`
  line `311 of the Constitution, and to such rules as the ^1[State Government] may from time to time make`
  line `under this Act, the Inspector-General, Deputy Inspectors-General, Assistant Inspector-General and`
  line `District Superintendents of Police may at any time dismiss, suspend or reduce any police-officer of the`
  line `subordinate ranks] whom they shall think remiss or negligent in the discharge of his duty, or unfit for`
  line `the same;`
  line
  line `^4[or may award any one or more of the following punishments to any police-officer ^5[of the`
  line `subordinate ranks] who shall discharge his duty in a careless or negligent manner, or who by any act`
  line `of his own shall render himself unfit for the discharge thereof, namely: --`
  line
  line `(a) fine to any amount not exceeding one months pay;`
  line
  line `(b) confinement to quarters for a term not exceeding fifteen days, with or without punishmentdrill, extra guard, fatigue or other duty;`
  line
  line `(c) deprivation of good-conduct pay;`
  line
  line `(d) removal from any office of distinction or special emolument.]^6`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for certain words.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950 (as amended by C.O. 29), for "Subject to such rules".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 2, for certain words.v`
  line `5. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `6. For clause (e), applicable to certain areas in the U.P., see U.P. Act 2 of 1944.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (46938)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Certificates to police officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46938&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1Every police-officer ^2[appointed to the police force other`
  line `than an officer mentioned in section 4] shall receive on his appointment a certificate in the from`
  line `annexed to this Act under the seal of the Inspector-General or such other officer as the InspectorGeneral shall appoint, by virtue of which the person holding such certificate shall be vested with the`
  line `powers, functions, and privileges of a police-officer.`
  line
  line `Surrender of certificate.--^3[Such certificate shall cease to have effect whenever the person`
  line `named in it ceases for any reason to be a police-officer, and, on his ceasing to be such an officer, shall`
  line `be forthwith surrendered by him to any officer empowered to receive the same.`
  line
  line `A police-officer shall not by reason of being suspended from office cease to be a police-officer.`
  line `During the term of such suspension the powers, functions and privileges vested in him as a policeofficer shall be in abeyance, but he shall continue subject to the same responsibilities, discipline and`
  line `penalties and to the same authorities, as if he had not been suspended.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. As to enrolment, maintenance and discipline of --`
  line
  line `(1) the Military Police-force employed in--`
  line
  line `(a) the Andaman and Nicobar Islands, see the Andaman and Nicobar Islands Military Police (Disbandment ) Regulation, 1946 (3 of 1946);`
  line
  line `(b) Assam, see the Assam Rifles Act, 1941 (5 of 1941);`
  line
  line `(c) Bengal, see the Eastern Frontier Rifles (Bengal Battalion) Act, 1920 (Ben. 2 of 1920);`
  line
  line `(2) the Punjab Frontier Police-officers, see the Punjab Frontier Police-officer Regulation, 1893 (7 of 1893);`
  line
  line `(3) the Calcutta and Suburban Police, see the Calcutta Police Act, 1866 (Ben. 4 of 1866) and the Calcutta Suburban`
  line `Police Act, 1866 (Ben. 2 of 1866);`
  line
  line `(4) the Police establishment in municipal areas in the U.P., see the U.P. Municipalities Act, 1916 (U.P. 2 of 1916);`
  line
  line `(5) the Police establishment in municipal areas in the Punjab, see the Punjab Municipal Act, 1911 (Pun. 3 of 1911);`
  line
  line `(6) the Rural Police in the Sonthal Parganas, see the Sonthal Parganas Rural Police Regulation, 1910 (4 of 1910);`
  line
  line `(7) the Rural Police in Chota Nagpur, see the Chota Nagpur Rural Police Act, 1914 (B. & O. 1 of 1914);`
  line
  line `(8) the U.P. Special Armed Constabulary, see the U.P. Special Armed Constabulary Act, 1942 (U.P. 5 of 1942);`
  line
  line `(9) the Delhi Special Police Establishment, see the Delhi Special Police Establishment Act, 1946 (25 of 1946); and`
  line
  line `(10) Delhi Police, see, Delhi Police Act, 1978 (34 of 1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "so appointed".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 3, for the second paragraph.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (46939)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Police-officers not to resign without leave or two months’ notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46939&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No police-officer shall`
  line `be at liberty to withdraw himself from the duties of his office unless expressly allowed to do so by the`
  line `District Superintendent or by some other officer authorised to grant such permission or, without the`
  line `leave of the District Superintendent, to resign his office unless he shall have given to his superior`
  line `officer notice in writing, for a period of not less than two months, of his intention to resign.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (46940)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Police-officers not to engage in other employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46940&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No police-officer shall engage in any`
  line `employment or office whatever other than his duties under this Act, unless expressly permitted to do`
  line `so in writing by the Inspector-General.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (46941)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46941&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `[Police superannuation fund.] Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1874 (16 of 1874) s. 1`
  line `and Sch., Pt. I.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (46942)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of Inspector-General to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46942&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Inspector-General of Police may, from`
  line `time to time, subject to the approval of the ^1`
  line `[State Government], frame such orders and rules as he`
  line `shall deem expedient relative to the organization, classification and distribution of the police-force, the`
  line `places at which the members of the force shall reside, and the particular services to be performed by`
  line `them; their inspection, the description of arms, accoutrements and other necessaries to be furnished to`
  line `them; the collecting and communicating by them of intelligence and information; and all such other`
  line `orders and rules relative to the police-force as the Inspector-General shall, from time to time, deem`
  line `expedient for preventing abuse or neglect of duty, and for rendering such force efficient in the`
  line `discharge of its duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (46943)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Additional police-officer employed at cost of individuals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46943&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for the`
  line `Inspector-General of Police, or any Deputy Inspector-General, or Assistant Inspector-General, or for`
  line `the District Superintendent, subject to the general direction of the Magistrate of the district, on the`
  line `application of any person showing the necessity thereof, to depute any additional number of policeofficers to keep the peace at any place within the general police-district, and for such time as shall be`
  line `deemed proper. Such force shall be exclusively under the orders of the District Superintendent, and`
  line `shall be at the charge of the person making the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be lawful for the person on whose application such deputation shall have been`
  line `made, on giving one months notice in writing to the Inspector-General, Deputy Inspector-General, or`
  line `Assistant Inspector-General, or to the District Superintendent, to require that the police-officers so`
  line `deputed shall be withdrawn; and such person shall be relieved from the charge of such additional force`
  line `from the expiration of such notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (46944)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Appointment of additional force in the neighbourhood of railway and other works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government"which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46944&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any railway, canal or other public work, or any manufactory or commercial`
  line `concern shall be carried on, or be in operation in any part of the country, and it shall appear to the`
  line `Inspector-General that the employment of an additional police-force in such place is rendered`
  line `necessary by the behaviour or reasonable apprehension of the behaviour of the persons employed`
  line `upon such work, manufactory or concern, it shall be lawful for the Inspector-General, with the consent`
  line `of the ^1`
  line `[State Government], to depute such additional force to such place, and to employ the same so`
  line `long as such necessity shall continue, and to make orders, from time to time, upon the person having`
  line `the control or custody of the funds used in carrying on such work, manufactory or concern, for the`
  line `payment of the extra force so rendered necessary, and such person shall thereupon cause payment to`
  line `be made accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (46945)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Quartering of additional police in disturbed or dangerous districts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46945&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Quartering of additional police in disturbed or dangerous districts.((1) It`
  line `shall be lawful for the ^2[State Government], by proclamation to be notified in the Official Gazette, and`
  line `in such other manner as the ^2[State Government] shall direct, to declare that any area subject to its`
  line `authority has been found to be in a disturbed or dangerous state, or that, from the conduct of the`
  line `inhabitants of such area or of any class or section of them, it is expedient to increase the number of`
  line police.
  line
  line `(2) It shall thereupon be lawful for the Inspector-General of Police, or other officer authorised by`
  line `the ^2[State Government] in this behalf, with the sanction of the ^2`
  line `[State Government], to employ any`
  line `police-force in addition to the ordinary fixed complement to be quartered in the area specified in such`
  line `proclamation as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (5) of this section, the cost of such additional policeforce shall be borne by the inhabitants of such area described in the proclamation.`
  line
  line `(4) The Magistrate of the district, after such enquiry as he may deem necessary, shall apportion`
  line `such cost among the inhabitants who are, as aforesaid, liable to bear the same and who shall not have`
  line `been exempted under the next succeeding sub-section. Such apportionment shall be made according to`
  line `the Magistrates judgement of the respective means within such area of such inhabitants.`
  line
  line `(5) It shall be lawful for the ^2[State Government] by order to exempt any persons or class or section`
  line `of such inhabitants from liability to bear any portion of such cost.`
  line
  line `(6) Every proclamation issued under sub-section (1) of this section shall state the period for which`
  line `it is to remain in force, but it may be withdrawn at any time or continued from time to time for a`
  line `further period or periods as the ^2[State Government] may in each case think fit to direct.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "inhabitants" shall include persons who themselves`
  line `or by their agents or servants occupy or hold land or other immoveable property within such area, and`
  line `landlords who themselves or by their agents or servants collect rents direct from raiyats or occupiers`
  line `in such area, notwithstanding that they do not actually reside therein.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 4, for the section 15.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (46981)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 16
  title `Awarding compensation to sufferers from misconduct of inhabitants or persons interested in land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46981&sectionno=15A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Awarding compensation to sufferers from misconduct of inhabitants or`
  line `persons interested in land.(1) If, in any area in regard to which any proclamation notified`
  line `under the last preceding section is in force, death or grievous hurt or loss of, or damage to, property`
  line `has been caused by or has ensued from the misconduct of the inhabitants of such area or any class or`
  line `section of them it shall be lawful for any person, being an inhabitant of such area, who claims to have`
  line `suffered injury from such misconduct to make, within one month from the date of the injury or such shorter period as may be prescribed, an application for compensation to the Magistrate of the district`
  line `or of the sub-division of a district within which such area is situated.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall thereupon be lawful for the Magistrate of the district, with the sanction of the ^2[State`
  line `Government] after such enquiry as he may deem necessary, and whether any additional police-force`
  line `has or has not been quartered in such area under the last preceding section, to`
  line
  line `(a) declare the persons to whom injury has been caused by or has ensued from such`
  line misconduct;
  line
  line `(b) fix the amount of compensation to be paid to such persons and the manner in which it is to`
  line `be distributed among them; and`
  line
  line `(c) assess the proportion in which the same shall be paid by the inhabitants of such area other`
  line `than the applicant who shall not have been exempted from liability to pay under the next`
  line `succeeding sub-section:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Magistrate shall not make any declaration or assessment under this sub-section,`
  line `unless he is of opinion that such injury as aforesaid has arisen from a riot or unlawful assembly within`
  line `such area, and that the person who suffered the injury was himself free from blame in respect of the`
  line `occurrences which led to such injury.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be lawful for the ^2[State Government], by order, to exempt any persons or class or`
  line `section of such inhabitants from liability to pay any portion of such compensation.`
  line
  line `(4) Every declaration or assessment made or order passed by the Magistrate of the district under`
  line `sub-section (2) shall be subject to revision by the Commissioner of the Division or the ^2[State`
  line `Government], but save as aforesaid shall be final.`
  line
  line `(5) No civil suit shall be maintainable in respect of any injury for which compensation has been`
  line `awarded under this section.`
  line
  line `(6) Explanation."In this section the word inhabitants shall have the same meaning as in the last`
  line `preceding section.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 15-A.--In the Police Act, 1861 (Act 15 of 1861), in its application to`
  line `Amendment the State of Orissa, for section 15-A, the following section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `15-A. Awarding compensation to sufferers from misconduct of inhabitants of any area.--(1)`
  line `If, any area, death or grievous hurt Awarding or loss of or damage to property (including public`
  line `property) has been caused by or has-ensued from sufferers the misconduct of the inhabitants of such`
  line `area or any class or section of them or from the failure inhabitants on their part to render assistance in`
  line `preventing such loss or damage, it shall be lawful for any person who claims to have suffered injury,`
  line `loss or case from such misconduct or failure, to make within one month from the date of the injury,`
  line `loss or damage, as the case may be, an application for compensation to the Magistrate of the district`
  line `within which such area is Situated.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall thereupon be lawful for the Magistrate of the district, with the sanction of the State`
  line `Government, after such enquiry as he may deem necessary, and whether any additional Police Force`
  line `has or, has not been quartered in such area under the last preceding section to--`
  line
  line `(a) declare the limits of the area the inhabitants of which have, in his opinion, been guilty`
  line `of such misconduct or failure;`
  line
  line `(b) declare the persons to whom injury, loss or damage has been caused by or has ensued`
  line `from such misconduct or failure,`
  line
  line `(c) fix the amount of compensation to be paid to such person and where there are More`
  line `than one such person, the manner in which it is to be distributed among them; and`
  line
  line `(d) assess the proportion in which the same 'shall be paid by the inhabitants (other than the`
  line `applicant) of such area who shall not have been exempted under sub-Section (3) from the`
  line `liability to pay:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the applicant is a private individual, the Magistrate shall not make any`
  line `declaration unless he is of opinion that such injury, loss or damage as aforesaid has arisen from a riot`
  line `or unlawful assembly within such area and that the applicant was himself free from blame in respect`
  line `of the occurrence which led to the injury, loss or damage.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be lawful for the State Government, by order, to exempt any person or class or section`
  line `of such inhabitants from the liability to pay any portion of such compensation.`
  line
  line `(4) Every declaration or assessment made or order passed by the Magistrate of the district under`
  line `sub-section (2) shall be subject to revision by the Revenue Divisional Commissioner or the State`
  line `Government, but save as aforesaid, shall be final.`
  line
  line `(5) No civil suit shall be maintainable in respect of any injury, loss or damage for which`
  line `compensation has been awarded under this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation I--in this section--`
  line
  line `(a) “inhabitants” shall have the same meaning as in section 15;`
  line
  line `(b) “person” shall include the Central Government, the Government of any State, any Local`
  line `Authority, any Company, any Corporation and any Association or body of individuals, whether`
  line `incorporated or not;`
  line
  line `(c) “Public property” shall have reference to any property owned by or belonging to--`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government or the Government of any State;`
  line
  line `(ii) any local authority;`
  line
  line `(iii) Any corporation established under any is owned, controlled or managed, partly or`
  line `wholly, by the Central Government or any State Government;`
  line
  line `(iv) any Company in which not less than fifty-one per cent of the share capital is held by`
  line `the Central Government or any State Government or Jointly by more than one such`
  line `government; and`
  line
  line `(v) any autonomous body established under any law.`
  line
  line `Explanation II- An application under sub-section (1) maybe made--`
  line
  line `(a) In case of the Government, by such officer as the Government may authorize in that`
  line `behalf, and`
  line
  line `(b) In the case of any local authority , Company, Corporation, Association or body, by the`
  line `person who is in charge of the property.”`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 5 of 1976, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (46982)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Recovery of moneys payable under sections 13, 14, 15 and 15A, and disposal of same when recovered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46982&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^116. Recovery of moneys payable under sections 13, 14, 15 and 15A, and disposal of same`
  line `when recovered.(1) All moneys payable under sections 13, 14, 15 and 15A shall be coverable by`
  line `the Magistrate of the district in the manner provided by sections 386 and 387 of the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1882^2 (10 of 1882), for the recovery of fines, or by suit any competent`
  line Court.
  line
  line ^3
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) All moneys paid or recovered under section 15A shall be paid by the Magistrate of the district`
  line `to the persons to whom and in the proportions in which the same are payable under that section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 6, for section 16.`
  line
  line `2. See now ss. 421 and 422 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (Act 2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `3. Subs-section (2) omitted by the A.O. 1937. See however, para. 4 of the India and Burma (Transitory Provisions) Order`
  line 1937.
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (46948)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Special police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46948&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `When it shall appear that any unlawful assembly, or riot or`
  line `disturbance of the peace has taken place, or may be reasonably apprehended, and that the police-force`
  line `ordinarily employed for preserving the peace is not sufficient for its preservation and for the`
  line `protection of the inhabitants and the security of property in the place where such unlawful assembly or`
  line `riot or disturbance of the peace has occurred, or is apprehended, it shall be lawful for any police-`
  line `officer not below the rank of Inspector to apply to the nearest Magistrate to appoint so many of the`
  line `residents of the neighbourhood as such police-officers may require to act as special police-officers for`
  line `such time and within such limits as he shall deem necessary; and the Magistrate to whom such`
  line `application is made shall, unless he see cause to the contrary, comply with the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (46949)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Powers of special police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46949&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every special police-officer so appointed shall have the`
  line `same powers, privileges and protection, and shall be liable to perform the same duties and shall be`
  line `amenable to the same penalties, and be subordinate to the same authorities, as the ordinary officers of`
  line police.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (46950)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Refusal to serve as special police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46950&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `If any person being appointed a special policeofficer as aforesaid shall without sufficient excuse, neglect or refuse to serve as such, or to obey such`
  line `lawful order or direction as may be given to him for the performance of his duties, he shall be liable,`
  line `upon conviction before a Magistrate, to a fine not exceeding fifty rupees for every such neglect,`
  line `refusal or disobedience.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (46951)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Authority to be exercised by police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46951&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^120. Authority to be exercised by police-officers.—Police-officers enrolled under this Act shall`
  line `not exercise any authority, except the authority provided for a police-officer under this Act and any`
  line `Act which shall hereafter be passed for regulating criminal procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. For some cases in which the application of s. 20 has been restricted, see the Assam Police-officers Regulation, 1883 (2 of`
  line `1883), and s. 2 of the Punjab Frontier Police-officer Regulation, 1893 (7 of 1893).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (46952)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Village police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. The Bengal Chaukidari Act, 1856.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46952&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall affect any hereditary or other village`
  line `police-officer, unless such officer shall be enrolled as a police-officer under this Act. When so`
  line `enrolled, such officer shall be bound by the provisions of the last preceding section. No hereditary or`
  line `other village police-officer shall be enrolled without his consent and the consent of those who have the`
  line `right of nomination.`
  line
  line `Police-chaukidars in the Presidency of Fort William.—If any police-officer appointed under`
  line `^1Act XX of 1856 (to make better provision .`
  line `for the appointment and maintenance of Police-chaukidars`
  line `in Cities, Towns, Stations, Suburbs and Bazars in the Presidency of Fort William in Bengal) is`
  line `employed out of the district for which he shall have been appointed under that Act, he shall not be`
  line `paid out of the rates levied under the said Act for that district.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (46953)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Police-officers always on duty and may be employed in, any part of district.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46953&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `police-officer shall, for all purposes in this Act contained, be considered to be always on duty, and`
  line `may at any time be employed as a police-officer in any part of the general police-district.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (46954)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Duties of police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46954&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every police-officer promptly to obey and`
  line `execute all orders and warrants lawfully issued to him by any competent authority; to collect and`
  line `communicate intelligence affecting the public peace; to prevent the commission of offences and public`
  line `nuisances; to detect and bring offenders to justice and to apprehend all persons whom he is legally`
  line `authorized to apprehend, and for whose apprehension sufficient ground exists; and it shall be lawful`
  line `for every police-officer, for any of the purposes mentioned in this section, without a warrant, to enter`
  line `and inspect any drinking-shop, gaming-house or other place of resort of loose and disorderly`
  line characters.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 23-A.--In the Police Act, 1861, after section 23, the following new`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `23-A. Power in relation to cognizable offences in a running train.--Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), a Sub-Inspector of police,`
  line `posted to the mobile out-post of the Government Railway Police, shall, while performing duty in a`
  line `running train, exercise the powers of the officer-in-charge of the local Government Railway Policestation`
  line `for the purposes of investigation into cognizable offences committed in a running train and`
  line `when so exercising such powers, shall be deemed to be the officer-in-charge of such police-station`
  line `discharging the functions of such officer within the limits of that Police-station.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 21 of 1986, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (46955)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Police-officers may lay information, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46955&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for any police-officer to lay any`
  line `information before a Magistrate, and to apply for a summons, warrant, search warrant or such other`
  line `legal process as may by law issue against any person committing an offence ^1`
  line `* * *.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and to prosecute such person up to final judgment`
  line `" rep. by Act 10 of 1882, s. 2 and the Schedule 1(b).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (46980)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Police-officers to take charge of unclaimed property, and be subject to Magistrates orders as to disposal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46980&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every police-officer to take charge of all unclaimed`
  line `property, and to furnish an inventory thereof to the Magistrate of the district.`
  line
  line `The police-officers shall be guided as to the disposal of such property by such orders as they shall`
  line `receive from the Magistrate of the district.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (46957)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Magistrate may detain property and issue proclamation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46957&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Magistrate of the district`
  line `may detain the property and issue a proclamation, specifying the articles of which it consists, and`
  line `requiring any person who has any claim thereto to appear and establish his right to the same within six`
  line `months from the date of such proclamation.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) The provisions of section 525 of the ^2Code of Criminal Procedure, 1882 (10 of 1882), shall be`
  line `applicable to property referred to in this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 7.`
  line
  line `2. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), s. 459.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (46958)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Confiscation of property if no claimant appears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46958&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[27. Confiscation of property if no claimant appears.--(1) If no person shall within the period`
  line `allowed claim such property, or the proceeds thereof, if sold, it may, if not already sold under`
  line `sub-section (2) of the last preceding section, be sold under the orders of the Magistrate of the district.`
  line
  line `(2) The sale-proceeds of property sold under the preceding sub-section and the proceeds of`
  line `property sold under section 26 to which no claim has been established shall be ^2`
  line `[ at the disposal of the`
  line ^3
  line `[State] Government.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 8, for section 27.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "at the disposal of Govt."`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial".`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (46959)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Persons refusing to deliver up certificate, etc., on ceasing to be police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46959&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `person, having ceased to be an enrolled police-officer under this Act, who shall not forthwith deliver`
  line `up his certificate, and the clothing, accoutrements, appointments and other necessaries which shall`
  line `have been supplied to him for the execution of his duty, shall be liable, on conviction before a`
  line `Magistrate, to a penalty not exceeding two hundred rupees, or to imprisonment with or without hard`
  line `labour, for a period not exceeding six months, or to both.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (46960)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Penalties for neglect of duty, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46960&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Every police-officer who shall be guilty of any violation`
  line `of duty or wilful breach or neglect of any rule or regulation or lawful order made by competent`
  line `authority, or who shall withdraw from the duties of his office without permission, ^1`
  line `[or without having`
  line `given previous notice for the period of two months,] ^2`
  line `[or who, being absent on leave, shall fail, without`
  line `reasonable cause, to report himself for duty on the expiration of such leave,] or who shall engage`
  line `without authority in any employment other than his police-duty, or who shall be guilty`
  line `of cowardice, or who shall offer any unwarrantable personal violence to any person in his custody,`
  line `shall be liable, on conviction before a Magistrate, to a penalty not exceeding three months pay, or to`
  line `imprisonment with or without hard labour, for a period not exceeding three months, or to both.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. These words shall be deemed to have been rep. so long as the Police (Resignation of Office) Ordinance, 1942 (11 of`
  line `1942), remains in force: see s. 2 and the Schedule of that Ordinance.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (46961)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Regulation of public assemblies and processions and licensing of the same.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for section 30.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46961&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[30. Regulation of public assemblies and processions and licensing of the same.—(1) The District Superintendent or Assistant District Superintendent of Police may, as occasion requires, direct`
  line `the conduct of all assemblies and processions on the public roads, or in the public streets or`
  line `thoroughfares, and prescribe the routes by which, and the times at which, such processions may pass.`
  line
  line `(2) He may also, on being satisfied that it is intended by any persons or class of persons to convene`
  line `or collect an assembly in any such road, street or thoroughfare, or to form a procession which would,`
  line `in the judgment of the Magistrate of the district, or of the sub-division of a district, if uncontrolled, be`
  line `likely to cause a breach of the peace, require by general or special notice that the persons convening or`
  line `collecting such assembly or directing or promoting such procession shall apply for a licence.`
  line
  line `(3) On such application being made, he may issue a license specifying the names of the licensees`
  line `and defining, the conditions on which alone such assembly or such procession is to be permitted to`
  line `take place and otherwise giving effect to this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that no fee shall be charged on the application for, or grant of, any such licence.`
  line
  line `(4) Music in the streets.—He may also regulate the extent to which music may be used in the`
  line `streets on the occasion of festivals and ceremonies.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (46962)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 32
  title `Powers with regard to assemblies and processions violating conditions of license.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 11.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46962&sectionno=30A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[30A. Powers with regard to assemblies and processions violating conditions of license.-- (1) Any Magistrate or District Superintendent of Police or Assistant District Superintendent of Police or`
  line `Inspector of Police or any police-officer in charge of a station may stop any procession which violates`
  line `the conditions of a licence granted under the last foregoing section, and may order it or any assembly`
  line `which violates any such conditions as aforesaid to disperse.`
  line
  line `(2) Any procession or assembly which neglects or refuses to obey any order given under the last`
  line `preceding sub-section shall be deemed to be an unlawful assembly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (46963)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `Police to keep order in public roads, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46963&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the police to keep order on`
  line `the public roads, and in the public streets, thoroughfares, ghats and landing-places, and at all other`
  line `places of public resort, and to prevent obstructions on the occasions of assemblies and processions on`
  line `the public roads and in the public streets, or in the neighbourhood of places of worship, during the`
  line `time of public worship, and in any case when any road, street, thoroughfare, ghat or landing-place`
  line `may be thronged or may be liable to be obstructed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (46964)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Penalty for disobeying orders issued under last three sections, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "two" .`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46964&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every person opposing`
  line `or not obeying the orders issued under the last ^1`
  line `[three] preceding sections, or violating the conditions`
  line `of any license granted by the District Superintendent or Assistant District Superintendent of Police for`
  line `the use of music, or for the conduct of assemblies and processions, shall be liable, on conviction`
  line `before a Magistrate, to a fine not exceeding two hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (46965)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Saving of control of Magistrate of district.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "three".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46965&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in the last ^1`
  line `[four] preceding sections`
  line `shall be deemed to interfere with the general control of the Magistrate of the district over the matters`
  line `referred to therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (46966)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Punishment for certain offences on roads, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46966&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, on any road or in any`
  line `^1[open place or street or thoroughfare within the limits of any town to which this section shall be specially extended by the ^2[State Government], commits any of the following offences, to the obstruction, inconvenience, annoyance, risk, danger or damage of the ^3[residents or passengers] shall, on conviction before a Magistrate, be liable to a fine not exceeding fifty rupees, or to imprisonment`
  line `^4[with or without hard labour] not exceeding eight days;`
  line
  line `Power of police-officers.--and it shall be lawful for any police-officer to take into custody,`
  line `without a warrant, any person who within his view commits any of such offences, namely:--`
  line
  line `First.--Slaughtering cattle, furious riding, etc.--Any person who slaughters any cattle or cleans`
  line `any carcass; any person who rides or drives any cattle recklessly or furiously, or trains or breaks any`
  line `horse or other cattle:`
  line
  line `Second.--Cruelty to animals.--Any person who wantonly or cruelly beats, abuses or tortures any`
  line `animal:`
  line
  line `Third.-Obstructing passengers.--Any person who keeps any cattle or conveyance of any`
  line `kind standing longer than is required for loading or unloading or for taking up or setting down`
  line `passengers, or who leaves any conveyance in such a manner as to cause inconvenience or danger to`
  line `the public:`
  line
  line `Fourth.--Exposing goods for sale.--Any person who exposes any goods for sale:`
  line
  line `Fifth.--Throwing dirt into street.--Any person who throws or lays down any dirt, filth,`
  line `rubbish or any stones or building materials, or who constructs any cowshed, stable or the like, or who`
  line `causes any offensive matter to run from any house, factory, dungheap, or the like:`
  line
  line `Sixth.A--Being found drunk or riotous.--Any person who is found drunk or riotous or who is`
  line `incapable of taking care of himself:`
  line
  line `Seventh.--Indecent exposure of person.--Any person who wilfully and indecently exposes`
  line `his person, or any offensive deformity or disease, or commits nuisance by easing himself, or by`
  line `bathing or washing in any tank or reservoir not being a place set apart for that purpose:`
  line
  line `Eighth.--Neglect to protect dangerous places.--Any person who neglects to fence in or`
  line `duly to protect any well, tank or other dangerous place or structure.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 34-A of Act No. 5 of 1861-- For section 34-A of the Police Act, 1861, the`
  line `following section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"34-A. Compounding of offences under sections 32 and 34.--An offence punishable under`
  line `section 32 or section 34 may, subject to any general or special order of the State Government in this`
  line `behalf, be compounded by the District Superintendent of Police, either before or after the institution of`
  line `the prosecution, on realization of such amount of composition fee as he thinks fit, not exceeding the`
  line `maximum amount of fine fixed for the offence, and when the offence is so compounded--"`
  line
  line `(i) before the institution of the prosecution, the offender shall not be liable to prosecution for such`
  line `offence and shall, if in custody, be set at liberty ;`
  line
  line `(ii) before the institution of the prosecution, the composition shall amount to acquittal of the`
  line `offender."`
  line
  line `[Vide the Uttar Pradesh Act 35 of 1979, s. ]`
  line
  line `Abatement of certain trials.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, --`
  line
  line `(1) the trial of an accused for --`
  line
  line `(a) an offence punishable under --`
  line
  line `"(i) the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988; or"`
  line
  line `(ii) the Public Gambling Act, 1867, not being an offence punishable under section 3 of that`
  line `Act or an offence in respect of wagering punishable under section 13 of that Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) section 34 of the Police Act, 1861; or`
  line
  line `(iv) section 160 of the Indian Penal Code, 1860; or`
  line
  line `(b) any other offence punishable with fine only, or`
  line
  line `(2) a procedure, under section 107 or section 109 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973,`
  line `pending before a Magistrate on the date of commencement of this Act from before "December 31,`
  line `2015" shall abate.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Uttar Pradesh Act 35 of 1979, s. 9, and amended by Uttar Pradesh Act 29 of 2016 and 9`
  line `of 2018]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid.,`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950 for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 13, for "residents and passengers".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 1 of 1903, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (46967)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46967&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `* * * Any charge against a police-officer above the rank of a constable under`
  line `this Act shall be enquired into and determined only by an officer exercising the powers of a`
  line ^2Magistrate.
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Certain words rep. by Act 10 of 1882, s. 2 and the Schedule I(b).`
  line
  line `2. I.e., by a Magistrate of the first class. See s. 3 (1) of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (Act 2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (46968)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to prosecute under other law not affected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46968&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall be`
  line `construed to prevent any person from being prosecuted under any other Regulation or Act for any`
  line `offence made punishable by this Act, or from being liable under any other Regulation or Act or any`
  line `other or higher penalty or punishment than is provided for such offence by this Act:`
  line
  line `Proviso.—Provided that no person shall be punished twice for the same offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (46969)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `Recovery of penalties and fines imposed by Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46969&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1[37. Recovery of penalties and fines imposed by Magistrates.—The provisions of sections 64 to`
  line `70, both inclusive, of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and of sections 386 to 389, both inclusive, of the ^2Code of Criminal Procedure, 1882 (10 of 1882), with respect to fines, shall apply to`
  line `penalties and fines imposed under this Act .`
  line `on conviction before Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that, notwithstanding anything contained in section 65 of the first-mentioned Code, any`
  line `person sentenced to fine under section 34 of this Act may be imprisoned in default of payment of such`
  line `fine for any period not exceeding eight days.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 14, for sections 37, 38, 39 and 40.`
  line
  line `2. See now sections 421 to 424 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (Act 2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `1. See, however, paragraph 4 of the India and Burma (Transitory Provisions) Order, 1937. S. 41 Read as follows: —"All`
  line `sums paid for the service of process by police-officers, and all rewards, forfeitures and penalties or shares of rewards,`
  line `forfeitures and penalties which by law are payable to informers shall, when the information is laid by a police-officer, be paid`
  line `into the General Police Fund".`
  line
  line `2. So much of s. 42 (the portion printed in italics) as relates to the limitation of suits rep. by Act 9 of 1871, s. 2 and the`
  line `First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (46973)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 40
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Rewards to police and informers payable to General Police Fund.] Rep. by the A. O. 1937.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46973&sectionno=41&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (46974)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 41
  title `Limitation of actions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. I.e., by a Magistrate of the first class. See s. 3 (1) of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (Act 2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46974&sectionno=42&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `^142 Limitation of actions.—All actions and prosecutions against any person, which may be`
  line `lawfully brought for anything done or intended to be done under the provisions of this Act, or under`
  line `the general police-powers hereby given shall be commenced within three months after the act`
  line `complained of shall have been committed, and not otherwise; and notice in writing of such action end`
  line `of the cause thereof shell be given to the defendant, or to the District Superintendent or an Assistant`
  line `District Superintendent of the District in which the act was committed, one month at least before the`
  line `commencement of the action.`
  line
  line `Tender of amends.—No plaintiff shall recover in any such action if tender of sufficient amend`
  line `shall have been made before such action brought, or if a sufficient sum of money shall have been paid`
  line `into Court after such action brought, by or on behalf of the defendant, and, though a decree shall be`
  line `given for the plaintiff in any such action, such plaintiff shall not have costs against the defendant,`
  line `unless the Judge before whom the trial is held shall certify his approbation of the action.`
  line
  line `Proviso.—Provided always that no action shall in any case lie where such officers shall have been`
  line `prosecuted criminally for the same act.`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (46975)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 42
  title `Plea that act was done under warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46975&sectionno=43&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `When any action or prosecution shall be brought or`
  line `any proceedings held against any police-officer for any act done by him in such capacity, it shall be`
  line `lawful for him to plead that such act was done by him under the authority of a warrant issued by a`
  line Magistrate.
  line
  line `Such plea shall be proved by the production of the warrant directing the act, and purporting to be`
  line `signed by such Magistrate and the defendant shall thereupon be entitled to a decree in his favour,`
  line `notwithstanding any defect of jurisdiction in such Magistrate. No proof of the signature of such`
  line `Magistrate shall be necessary, unless the Court shall see reason to doubt its being genuine:`
  line
  line `Proviso.—Provided always that any remedy which the party may have against the authority`
  line `issuing such warrant shall not be affected by anything contained in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (46976)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 43
  title `Police-officers to keep diary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46976&sectionno=44&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every officer in charge of a policestation to keep a general diary in such form shall, from time to time, be prescribed by the ^1`
  line `[State Government] and to record therein all complaints and charges preferred, the names of all persons`
  line `arrested, the names of the complainants, the offences charged against them, the weapons or property`
  line `that shall have been taken from their possession or otherwise, and the names of the witnesses who`
  line `shall have been examined.`
  line
  line `The Magistrate of the district shall be at liberty to call for and inspect such diary.`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (46977)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 44
  title `State Government may prescribe form of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46977&sectionno=45&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The ^1`
  line `[State Government] may direct the`
  line `submission of such returns by the Inspector-General and other police-officers as to such ^1`
  line [State
  line `Government] shall seem proper, and may prescribe the form in which such returns shall made.`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (46978)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 45
  title `Scope of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46978&sectionno=46&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `^2[46. Scope of Act.(1) This Act shall not by its own operation take effect in any ^3presidency,`
  line `^4[State] or place. But the ^1[State Government] by an order to be published in the Official Gazette may`
  line `extend the whole or any part of this Act to any presidency, ^4[State] or place, and the whole or such`
  line `portion of this Act as shall be specified in such order shall thereupon take effect in such presidency,`
  line `^4[State] or place.`
  line
  line `(2) When the whole or any part of this Act shall have been extended, the ^1[State Government] may,`
  line `from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules consistent with this Act`
  line
  line `(a) to regulate the procedure to be followed by Magistrates and police-officers in the discharge`
  line `of any duty imposed upon them by or under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) to prescribe the time, manner and conditions within and under which claims for`
  line `compensation under section 15A are to be made, the particulars to be stated in such claims, the`
  line `manner in which the same are to be verified, and the proceedings (including local enquiries if`
  line `necessary) which are to be taken consequent thereon; and`
  line
  line `(c) generally, for giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this Act may from time to time be amended, added to or cancelled by the`
  line `^1[State Government].]`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 1895, s. 15, for section 46.`
  line
  line `3. In the States of Madras and Bombay there are special Police Acts, see the Madras District Police Act, 1859 (24 of 1859)`
  line `and the Bombay District Police Act, 1867 (Born. 7 of 1867). In the Lower Provinces of Bengal, Bengal Act 7 of 1869 is to`
  line `be read and taken as part of Act 5 of 1861, see s. 6 of the former Act.`
  line
  line `This Act has been extended under the power conferred by the original section to`
  line
  line `(1) the U. P. including Ajmer-Merwara then under that Government, see Notification No. 964 in the North-Western`
  line `Provinces Gazette, 1861, p. 634:`
  line
  line `[The orders as to enforcement of the Act in 27 districts in the U. P., in Hamirpur, Jalaun, Jhansi, Lalitpur,`
  line `Naini Tal (including the Tarai Parganas) and Almora and Garhwal, issued under the original s. 46, paragraph 2`
  line `(after the Act had been extended under paragraph 1 of that section to the whole province) are kept in force by s. 16 of Act`
  line `8 of 1895.]`
  line
  line `(2) Oudh, see Notification No. 34 in the North-Western Provinces Gazette, 1861, p. 1758 ;`
  line
  line `(3) the tract of land between Allahabad and Jubbulpore ceded in full sovereignty by certain Native States ;`
  line
  line `(4) the C. P., Districts of Nagpur, Raipur, Bhandara, Chanda and Chhindwara, Sironcha, Nimsar;`
  line
  line `(5) Bengal and Assam;`
  line
  line `(6) several districts in the Punjab, see Notification No. 971, dated 15th May, 1861, Calcutta Gazette, 18th May1861,`
  line `p. 1302.`
  line
  line `Under the power conferred by the section as it stood before the 1st April 1937, it has been extended as follows`
  line to--
  line
  line `(1) Madras: ss. 15, 15A, 16, 30, 30A, 31 and 32 of the Act have been extended to the whole of the Madras`
  line `Presidency, see Notification No. 728, dated 31st October 1895, Gazette of India, 1895, Pt. I., p. 876.`
  line
  line `(2) Eastern Dooars in the Goalpara District, see Notification No. 230, Gazette of India, 1897, Pt. 1, p. 198.`
  line
  line `(3) the North and South Lushai Hills and the tract known as Rutton Puiya's villages including Demagri (now known`
  line `as the Lushai Hills) see Gazette of India, 1898, Pt. 1, p. 370.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Province".`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (46979)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 46
  title `Authority of District Superintendent of Police over village police.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428&sectionId=46979&sectionno=47&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00038_186105_1523266889428
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for the`
  line ^1
  line `[State Government] in carrying this Act into effect in any part of the territories subject to such ^1`
  line [State
  line `Government], to declare that any authority which now is or may be exercised by the Magistrate of the`
  line `district over any village-watchman to or other village police-officer for the purposes of police, shall be`
  line `exercised, subject to the general control of the Magistrate of the district, by the District Superintendent`
  line `of Police.`
